  "texts": [
    "Values in each window of length w are normalized to have standard deviation of 1 to obtain amplitude invariance. 2.",
    "Each normalized window of length w is subjected to dimensionality reduction by the use of the truncated Fourier transform, keeping only the first l < w coefficients for further analysis.",
    "This step acts as a low pass filter, as higher order Fourier coefficients typically represent rapid changes like dropouts or noise. 3.",
    "Discretisation bins are derived through Multiple Coefficient Binning (MCB).",
    "It separately records the l distributions of the real and imaginary values of the Fourier transform."
